		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">Quaternionic geometries arise in several different areas of theoretical physics.  This proposal is principally concerned with quaternionic Kahler and hyperKahler manifolds and harmonic maps into these spaces.  One important construction is that of a moment map for a group of isometries and the corresponding  symmetry reduction; many moduli spaces arise in this way.  The resulting quotient spaces are often forced to be singular, but the nature of these singularities is currently poorly understood.  It is proposed to study the case of circle actions.  A variety of examples can be constructed and a thorough understanding of these should point to general results.Quaternionic Kahler manifolds admit special solutions (superminimal) of the harmonic map equations.  These have the special feature of being constructible via holomorphic geometry, in particular twistor theory.  The known compact examples of quaternionic Kahler manifolds may all be constructed from nilpotent orbits of simple Lie groups.  Relationships between different orbits will be studied with the object of describing the space of superminimal maps, and the related geometry will be pursued.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
